#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:343
msgid ""
"Do I need a ImageKit account to use the ImageKit plugin and can I try it "
"out for free?"
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:350
#. translators: %1$s: opening bold tag, %2$s: opening link tag, %3$s: closing
#. link tag, %4$s: closing bold tag
msgid ""
"To use the ImageKit plugin and all the functionality that comes with it, "
"you will need to have a ImageKit Account. %1$sIf you don't have an account "
"yet, %2$ssign up%3$s now for a free ImageKit account%4$s. You'll start with "
"generous usage limits and when your requirements grow, you can easily "
"upgrade to a plan that best fits your needs."
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:359
msgid "How does this plugin work?"
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:361
msgid ""
"The plugin makes your site faster by automatically delivering optimized "
"images and videos to your visitors. Every image gets converted to modern "
"formats like WebP and AVIF, compressed for faster loading, and served "
"through ImageKit's global CDN - all without you doing anything. Processing "
"happens entirely on ImageKit's servers, not yours, so your WordPress server "
"stays fast and responsive. Technically, the plugin rewrites your media URLs "
"on the fly to point to ImageKit instead of your WordPress server, so "
"images, videos, and optionally CSS/JS files are optimized and cached "
"globally for lightning-fast delivery."
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:365
msgid "What happens to my original WordPress files?"
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:367
msgid ""
"Your original files remain safe and untouched in WordPress. The plugin "
"delivers optimized versions through ImageKit without modifying your source "
"files. If you ever disable the plugin, your site will continue to work "
"normally using the original files."
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:371
msgid "Can I disable the plugin? Will my site break?"
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:373
msgid ""
"Yes, you can safely disable or uninstall the plugin at any time. Your site "
"will automatically fall back to serving files from WordPress, since the "
"plugin does not modify your original content. There is no lock-in or risk "
"to your website."
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:377
msgid "I've installed and set up the ImageKit plugin, what happens now?"
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:379
msgid ""
"If you left all the settings as default, the plugin will automatically "
"rewrite your media URLs to deliver them through ImageKit. Your images and "
"assets will be optimized and served via ImageKit, and you should begin "
"seeing improvements in performance across your site."
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:383
msgid "Do I need to migrate my existing media to ImageKit?"
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:385
msgid ""
"No migration is needed. The plugin automatically delivers your existing "
"WordPress media through ImageKit without any manual changes to old posts. "
"New uploads can be automatically sent to ImageKit based on your storage "
"settings, while existing files stay where they are and are served through "
"ImageKit for optimization."
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:389
msgid "Are my media uploads automatically sent to ImageKit?"
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:391
msgid ""
"Yes. When you upload media through the WordPress Media Library, the plugin "
"automatically offloads it to your ImageKit account. You can configure the "
"storage mode in General Settings to keep copies in both WordPress and "
"ImageKit, store a low-resolution version locally, keep files only in "
"ImageKit, or only in WordPress."
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:395
msgid ""
"Can I browse and insert assets from my ImageKit account directly in "
"WordPress?"
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:397
msgid ""
"Yes. The plugin adds an ImageKit tab to the WordPress media modal, allowing "
"you to browse, search, and select assets from your ImageKit media library. "
"Selected assets are imported into WordPress so you can insert them into "
"your posts and pages without re-uploading."
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:401
msgid "Does ImageKit support all image formats?"
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:403
msgid ""
"ImageKit supports all popular image formats that cover 99.99% of use cases. "
"On the settings page, you can further configure whether to allow or "
"disallow a particular file type to be loaded via ImageKit."
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:407
msgid ""
"I installed the plugin but Google PageSpeed Insights is still showing image "
"warnings"
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:411
#. translators: %1$s: opening link tag, %2$s: closing link tag
msgid ""
"This plugin automatically optimizes images and serves them in next-gen "
"formats including WebP and AVIF. However, it does not automatically resize "
"images to match your layout dimensions. This is usually because image "
"dimensions don't match your layout - use WordPress' %1$snative responsive "
"images feature%2$s or the plugin's Responsive Images settings to generate "
"properly sized breakpoints for different screen sizes."
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:418
msgid "Does this plugin support custom CNAME?"
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:420
msgid ""
"Yes, you can email developer@imagekit.io to configure a custom CNAME for "
"your account and then specify that in the plugin settings page."
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:424
msgid "Can I configure this plugin to use ImageKit for custom upload directories?"
msgstr ""

#: ui-definitions/settings-pages.php:426
msgid ""
"Yes, you can specify any number of custom directory locations on the plugin "
"settings page."
msgstr ""

